The paper deals with the problem of multiple-source adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of transfer learning. The paper presents new algorithms and theoretical contributions for solving this problem, which are likely to be of interest to researchers in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and statistical learning (cs.SD).
